				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="color: red"><span style="font-size: 18px; line-height: normal">Specialization Debate Thread</span></span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Assumptions</span>
<br />

<br />
All spells availible to our test subject
<br />
Only summoned focus items are used by our test subject
<br />
Resists by MOBs are not taken into account
<br />
Unless Specifically noted in an example specalization is not taken into account for mana cost
<br />
Due to unproven resist rates, and high debate on such, rains are ommited from this analysis
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Summoned Focus Items</span>
<br />

<br />
Lets look at adding our Summoned Focus Items since everyone has access to them.
<br />

<br />
Summoned Bracer - 20% damage bonus (using 10% due to random fluxuation)
<br />
Summoned Ring - 15% cast time reduction
<br />
Summoned Ear - 15% mana reduction (using 7.5% due to random fluxuation)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Spells</span>:
<br />

<br />
Evocation: Firebolt of Talon (Bolt), Sun Storm (Rain)
<br />

<br />
Conjouration: Sun Vortex (DD), Black Steel (DD), Ancient: Shock of Sun(DD), Shock of Fiery Blades (DD)
<br />

<br />
As you can see all magician DD spells from level 60 up are Conjouration.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Damage</span>:
<br />
<span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal">*Numbers in () are focused</span>
<br />
Fire Bolt of Talon: 2000 (2200)
<br />

<br />
Sun Vortex: 1550 (1705)
<br />
Black Steel: 1400 (1540)
<br />
Ancient: Shock of Sun: 1150 (1265)
<br />
Shock of Fiery Blades: 1005 (1106)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Mana Cost</span>:
<br />
<span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal">*Numbers in () are focused</span>
<br />
Fire Bolt of Talon: 500 (463)
<br />

<br />
Sun Vortex: 395 (365)
<br />
Black Steel: 360 (333)
<br />
Ancient: Shock of Sun: 285 (264)
<br />
Shock of Fiery Blades: 334(309)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Base Cast Time</span>:
<br />
<span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal">*Numbers in () are focused</span>
<br />
Fire Bolt of Talon: 7 (6)
<br />

<br />
Sun Vortex: 6.3 (5.4)
<br />
Black Steel: 6.2 (5.1)
<br />
Ancient: Shock of Sun: 6 (5.1)
<br />
Shock of Fiery Blades: 6.8 (5.78)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Base Damage Per Mana</span>:
<br />
<span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal">*Numbers in () are focused</span>
<br />
Fire Bolt of Talon: 4 (4.75)
<br />

<br />
Sun Vortex: 3.92 (4.67)
<br />
Black Steel: 3.88 (4.62)
<br />
Ancient: Shock of Sun: 4.03 (4.79)
<br />
Shock of Fiery Blades: 3 (3.31)
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Damage Per Second</span>:
<br />
<span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal">*Numbers in () are focused</span>
<br />
Fire Bolt of Talon: 285.71 (366.66)
<br />

<br />
Sun Vortex: 246.03 (315.74)
<br />
Black Steel: 225.80 (301.96)
<br />
Ancient: Shock of Sun: 191.66 (248.03)
<br />
Shock of Fiery Blades: 147.79 (191.34)
<br />

<br />
Now what do all these numbers mean?  Blankly saying Firebolt of Tallon is the best, simply because it has the biggest base damage, is inaccurate and misleading.  Lets look at what traditionally tells us how "good" a nuke is, Base Damage and Damage per Mana.  These figures show us the following:
<br />

<br />
Highest Base Damage: Firebolt of Tallon 2000 (2200)
<br />
2nd Highest: Sun Vortex 1550 (1705)
<br />
Ratio - FoT is 22.5% (22.5%) more damaging than Sun Vortex
<br />

<br />
Highest Damage per Mana Ratio: Firebolt of Tallon 4 (4.75)
<br />
2nd Highest: Sun Vortex: 3.92 (4.67)
<br />
Ratio - FoT is 2% (1.6%) more mana efficent than Sun Vortex
<br />

<br />
At this point, it is a reasonable conclusion FoT is the best nuke due to its superior base damage, abeit not much more efficent than Sun Vortex.  However, we should go further and qualify this assertion.
<br />

<br />
Base Mana Cost tells us:
<br />

<br />
Fire Bolt of Talon: 500 (463)
<br />
Sun Vortex: 395 (365)
<br />

<br />
Using the focused values, we see that for every FoT cast, 463 - 365 = 98 more mana is used rather than casting Sun Vortex.  Therefore, for every 4 casts of FoT you can cast a "mana free" Sun Vortex.  So lets look at it cast by cast...
<br />
<span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal">*Note: Seconds used = cast time + recast time + prior time used</span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Cast 1</span>
<br />
FoT 463 mana used, 2,200 damage done, 8.25 seconds used (6 cast time + 2.25 recast time + 0)
<br />
SV 365 mana used, 1,705 damage done, 7.65 seconds used (5.4 cast time + 2.25 recast time + 0)
<br />
Difference: FoT did 495 more damage for 98 more mana 0.6 seconds slower than Sun Vortex.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Cast 2</span>
<br />
FoT 926 mana used, 4,400 damage done, 16.5 seconds used (6 cast time + 2.25 recast time + 8.25)
<br />
SV 730 mana used, 3,410 damage done, 15.3 seconds used (5.4 cast time + 2.25 recast time + 7.65)
<br />
Difference: FoT did 990 more damage for 196 more mana 1.2 seconds slower than Sun Vortex.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Cast 3</span>
<br />
FoT 1,389 mana used, 6,600 damage done, 24.75 seconds used 
<br />
SV 1,095 mana used, 5,115 damage done, 22.95 seconds used 
<br />
Difference: FoT did 1,485 more damage for 294 more mana 1.8 seconds slower than Sun Vortex.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Cast 4</span>
<br />
FoT 1,852 mana used, 8,800 damage done, 33 seconds used 
<br />
SV 1,460 mana used, 6,820 damage done, 30.6 seconds used 
<br />
Difference: FoT did 1,980 more damage for 392 more mana 2.4 seconds slower than Sun Vortex.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Cast 5</span>
<br />
(at this point you can cast Sun Vortex from the mana saved over the previous 4 FoT )
<br />
FoT 2,315 mana used, 11,000 damage done, 41.25 seconds used 
<br />
SV 1,825 mana used, 8,525 damage done, 38.25 seconds used 
<br />

<br />

<br />
This proves that, in its raw state with only summoned focus items and not accounting for specialization, FoT does more damage in slightly more time than Sun Vortex.  This is raw data, it does not take into account specialization.  Now lets do just that here.  Specialization reduces mana costs by 10% at 200 and 2.5% at 50.
<br />
<span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal">Its worth noting that specialization savings on FoT are 46.3 for the Evocation mage and 11.5 for the Conjouration mage.</span>
<br />

<br />
For the Evocation mage Fire Bolt of Tallon cast:
<br />
4 times, 1667 mana used, 8,800 damage done in 33 seconds 
<br />
For the Conjouration mage Firebolt of Tallon cast: 
<br />
4 times, 1,808 mana used, 8,800 damage done in 33 seconds
<br />

<br />
For the Evocation mage Sun Vortex cast:
<br />
4 times, 1,424 mana used, 6,820 damage done in 30.6 seconds 
<br />
For the Conjouration mage Sun Vortex cast: 
<br />
4 times, 1,316 mana used, 6,820 damage done in 30.6 seconds
<br />

<br />
Illustrating that specialization Evoc or Conj means -->> Little to nothing at all in terms of nuking other than this single statement:
<br />

<br />
As an Evocation Mage casting Firebolt of Tallon, I can deal the same damage in the same amount of time as my conjouration counterpart for 34.8 less mana per cast.  Also as an evocation mage, I forgo any benefit of mana savings on all of my pet, pet heal, or summon spells.
<br />

<br />
Therefore, it is my assertation that unless you chain FoT for long periods with little to no downtime availible, Conjouration is a more beneficial specialization.  However, for those magi who do cast Firebolt of Tallon for long extended periods with little to no downtime availible that Evocation would be a more beneficial specialization.<br />_________________<br /><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" align="left"><tr><td><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26797"><img src="http://www.jtbates.net/everquest/images/jtshieldtransparent.gif" border="0" /></a></td><td><a href="http://www.fohguild.org">[Fires of Heaven]</a> - <a href="http://forum.magecompendium.com/tower/viewtopic.php?t=3239">[Magician's Tower Library]</a></td></tr></table><br></span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Jaytee Bushwacker on Fri Jul 11, 2003 2:21 pm; edited 7 times in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
