<br />

<br />
...and as we come to the end of our discussion, I have one Final Thought(tm).  As an Evocation Mage you have no alternative to the Big Bang on FR MOBs, any MR nukes you toss out are not within your specialization so on FR MOBs you are at a complete disadvantage.  Your Conjouration based friend can cast MR nukes, but also on completely MR MOBs he can cast FR nukes within his specialization, i.e. Ancient: Shock of Sun and Shock of Fiery Blades.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Well, that's overstated more than a wee bit.  Max difference between 200 spec and 50 spec, either way, is 7.5% per cast.  I use MR nukes just fine, thank you, even though I'm spec'ed evoc.  Yes, I pay 7.5% more per cast than a conj spec mage, but that adds up to 1 more nuke every 12 casts... not that big a deal, in my opinion.
<br />

<br />
When I get Black Steel, my opinion may very well change.  But for now, I don't see a huge difference.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=171313&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Eloina Pyromancer</span></a> -- Arch Mage
