			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The difference is bigger than you think.  Saving mana is the indirect equivalent to mana regeneration + mana pool enhancement.
<br />

<br />
Why?  Because if you spend less mana on your spells, the current mana regen that you do have is <span style="font-style: italic">worth</span> more.  That same mana regen means a new nuke faster.
<br />

<br />
I believe a 7.5% saving on all spells you cast would effectively mean that your mana regen is 7.5% higher, and your mana pool is 7.5% larger.
<br />

<br />
If you were to *never* sit down and meditate, and you always had KEI, your mana regen would raise by 1.05 with specialize 200.  If you had a 3k mana pool (most of us 65's have much more), you would seemingly gain 225 more mana.
<br />

<br />
Think about that <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=106710" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.lehigh.edu/~dsf3/EQ/rhionsligo.jpg" border="0" />
<br />
My Character Profile</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
