True and importance does not necessarily imply popularity.  Perhaps I mistated, I wanted to put this "popular" topic to bed so to speak.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
Fair enough.
<br />

<br />
From my point of view, there are two types of spellcasting... 1) casting spells when I have no pending event to spur mana regen, 2) casting spells when I must regen mana as quickly as possible.
<br />

<br />
The first of these is the condition under which most conjuration spells are cast.  Do I care whether it takes me 6 seconds more to regen the mana from casting Gift of Xev?  Not really.  Specialization doesn't really matter under those conditions.
<br />

<br />
The second condition is when most combat spells are cast, and your figures show that there is relatively little difference between the two specialization choices.  At the most, a 7.5% difference in mana usage.
<br />

<br />
Now, reality is that I'm bound more by agro then I am mana in the high-end game.  I don't chaincast all that much... only when I absolutely need to.  I can't remember the last time that I burned through an entire bar of mana.  When I do use a lot of mana, I canni-pet to regain it back... something that I do easily even though I'm spec'ed evoke.
<br />

<br />
So, my point is fundamentally this: given our mana regen capabilities with cannipet, and the fact that we're bound by agro rather than mana for most encounters, specializing one way or the other is essentially a personal preference.
<br />

<br />
It has very little impact on the game, overall.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=171313&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Eloina Pyromancer</span></a> -- Arch Mage
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=502692&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Zashir Swiftpaw</span></a> -- Animist
<br />
Torvonnilous</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Eloina Pyromancer on Fri Mar 28, 2003 10:33 pm; edited 1 time in total</span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
