			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For the sake of being devil's advocate, let me state a couple advantages of evoc:
<br />

<br />
1. Speed. Evoc spells generally allow one to dump more short run dps into a mob then conj dds. Sunstorm is blindingly fast for short run dps, and firebolt is pretty impressive. If the mob must die asap, evoc is usuually king.
<br />

<br />
2. Speed = efficiency. One can turn the above speed into efficiency by using right-click nukers during the time saved.
<br />

<br />
3. Level/availability quirks. At levels 61-62 evoc is a particularly strong choice. If black steel simply isn't available, or a mage for whatever reason has decided to stall at level 62, evoc may be a good choice. Simularly evoc is a strong choice from levels 49-56 (setting aside pet cannabilization) Furthermore sun vortex and ancient:nuke should NOT be considered standard fare for mages. 
<br />

<br />
4. Aggro. I am convinced that rain spells do less aggro per point of damage then dd nukes. I'm conj speced, and rains are my standard nuke of choice on most raid boss mobs. In turn, if someone WANTS to generate aggro (aggro kiting) firebolt of tallon can't be beat.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
